    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "“O Allah, forgive him, have mercy on him, grant him well-being, pardon him, honour his resting-place, expand his entrance, wash him with water, ice and hail, cleanse him of sins as a white garment is cleansed of dirt, replace his home with a better one, his family with a better one, his spouse with a better spouse, admit him to Paradise, and protect him from the punishment of the grave and the Fire.”"
    },
    {
      "type": "section_title",
      "text": "Prayer for the Absent"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If it is not possible to perform janazah on someone present, the same prayer may be offered in absence by an imam and congregation. It was related in authentic hadiths that the Prophet (ﷺ) did this upon the death of an-Najashi in Abyssinia. The procedure is identical except that the bodies are not present before the imam.",
